# 📉 Customer Churn Analysis

## 📌 Objective
The goal of this project is to analyze customer data and identify key factors leading to churn. This helps businesses proactively address churn risks and improve customer retention strategies.

## 🛠️ Tools & Technologies
- Python
- Jupyter Notebook
- Pandas, NumPy
- Matplotlib, Seaborn
- Scikit-learn (for classification)

## 📊 Key Tasks Performed
- Cleaned and preprocessed raw churn dataset
- Performed exploratory data analysis (EDA)
- Identified correlations between features and churn
- Built and evaluated machine learning models (Logistic Regression, Decision Tree, etc.)
- Suggested actionable insights to reduce churn

## 📌 Insights
- Tenure and service-related features were strong indicators of churn.
- Customers with multiple services and high monthly charges showed higher churn rates.

## 🧑‍💻 About Me
I completed this project as part of my data analytics learning path to apply Python skills in solving a real-world business problem.
